casebody.data:
State v. George Levine.

February Term, 1931.

Present: Powers, C. J., Slack, Moulton, and Thompson, JJ. Opinion filed April 23, 1931. Deane C. Davis for the respondent. Lawrence C. Jones, Attorney General, and C. O. Granan, State’s attorney, for the State. *323Slack, J.

This case presents the same question that was raised in State v. Brown, ante page 313, 154 Atl. 579, came to this Court in the same way and was heard with that ease. The decision in that case controls this.

Judgment affirmed, and cause remanded.
